title: Cut Copy - Bright Like Neon Love (2004) [LAME VBR]
description: The debut by Melbourne\&#039;s Cut Copy is a collection of dream and love-laden tunes pulled together with Dan Whitford\&#039;s inside-out knowledge of 80\&#039;s flavored synths and studio trickery. Influences range from house to low-slung, fuzzed up punk garage, and seminal 80\&#039;s raincoat-wearing Mancunian electro-pop to nouveau disco, often within one song. Impossible to pigeonhole. Pop and dance. Happy sad. Simple yet complicated. Sincere yet cool. Naive but clever.
